185
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,000
 as Boris has said

186
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:04,000
 but also because we

187
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,000
 intelligently used the EU funds

188
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:08,000
 especially the social fund part

189
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:10,000
 which helped us

190
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:12,000
 to be able to stand

191
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:14,000
 strongly behind our citizens

192
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,000
 and behind our economy.

193
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,000
 And where do we find

194
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,000
 ourselves today?

195
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,000
 Today we find ourselves

196
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,000
 in the situation where

197
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:25,000
 COVID, energy crisis, food crisis

198
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,000
 and inflatory pressure

199
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,000
 are being dealt with.

200
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:30,000
 I wouldn't say that we have

201
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,000
 tamed them completely

202
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,000
 because there are many, many

203
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,000
 challenges still there.

204
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,000
 But what did we do

205
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:38,000
 in a short period of time?

206
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:43,000
 One, we avoided economic downturns.

207
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:44,000
 On the contrary,

208
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,000
 we showed resilience,

209
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,000
 agility.

210
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:49,000
 Croatia's rise of the GDP

211
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:52,000
 in 2021 went above 13%.

212
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:55,000
 Last year it was above 6%.

213
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,000
 This year we already reviewed

214
00:08:57,000 --> 00:09:00,000
 our estimation from 0.7% to 2.2%.

215
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,000
 But when I look at the results

216
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,000
 of the first quarter

217
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:06,000
 which is 2.8% according to our statistics

218
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:09,000
 and 2.6% according to the harmonized

219
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,000
 EU statistics,

220
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:12,000
 that means that certainly

221
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,000
 and especially speaking

222
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,000
 from Dubrovnik

223
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,000
 and knowing what will be

224
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,000
 the effect of the Eurozone

225
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:18,000
 and Schengen to our tourism

226
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,000
 and its contribution

227
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,000
 to the growth of the GDP,

228
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:22,000
 the growth will be even higher.

229
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,000
 There is no doubt about it.

230
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:31,000
 Secondly, the situation that we have dealt with

231
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:34,000
 at the European Union level

232
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:39,000
 in terms of creating new energy interconnections

233
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:41,000
 in an incredibly fast manner

234
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:45,000
 has ensured us the independence

235
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:47,000
 in terms of energy supply.

236
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:49,000
 One of our best decisions

237
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,000
 in the first mandate

238
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:54,000
 was to cut the 40 years long debate

239
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:56,000
 in the Croatian energy sector

240
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,000
 whether we do need

241
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,000
 or whether we don't need

242
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,000
 the liquefied natural gas terminal

243
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,000
 at the island of Kerk.

244
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,000
 We said we need it.

245
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:04,000
 We asked the European Union

246
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,000
 to help us with the financing.

247
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:09,000
 We got a grant of 101 billion euros.

248
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,000
 The government said

249
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,000
 we will match it

250
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,000
 with another 100 million euros

251
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,000
 coming from the budget.

252
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:16,000
 the Croatian electricity company

253
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:18,000
 and the Croatian gas transport company

254
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:21,000
 added another 34 or 35 million

255
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:24,000
 and for 235 million euros

256
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:27,000
 we have 2.9 billion cubic meters capacity

257
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,000
 LNG ship in Kerk

258
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,000
 with our network of the pipelines.

259
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,000
 Now we made a decision

260
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:34,000
 to invest even more into it

261
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,000
 another 25 million

262
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:37,000
 in order to elevate its capacity

263
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,000
 to 6.1 billion cubic meters

264
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:41,000
 not because of our own needs

265
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,000
 because Croatia

266
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:45,000
 when we have the full swing consumption

267
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,000
 of our households

268
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,000
 of our businesses

269
